text: We’ve gotten deep dish and regular pizza from here and it’s always been great. Last time we fell in love with the tiramisu. I did an online order to pick up. I ordered 2 tiramisu, when I got home only one was in the bag. I called the store …More

text: Nice and clean. Ingredients were fresh and tasty. We ordered the Chicago Style Deep Dish. Wasn't impressed with the thickness of the dough. It felt like a regular pizza with an extra thick crust to make it appear it Chicago style. Again, it …More

text: Be careful when you order, they don’t stick to traditional recipe but also don’t mention that on the menu. My son has a tomato allergy so I read everything on the menu before I order. We ordered a calzone, sounds safe, well it was not. It …More

name: Leggs_82 Leggs_82
text: I'm a cheese and sausage girl. This is Chicago style pizza and I'm a new fan! Nice thin crispy crust with good sausage and not a lot of sauce.

name: Ivon Neville
text: We started ordering from Rosati’s at the beginning of the pandemic since they were “within a 10 mile radius” that delivered to us. While the pizza was good, not great, my kids seem to like it. We ordered online with no past problem. Zero …More

name: Marisa Martinez
text: We ordered a Chicago Style Deep Dish pizza with pepperoni, and it was just ok. Not very enjoyable to eat because the crust was too hard, like either it was kneaded too much or cooked too long, or both. The tomato sauce was WAY too salty, …More

name: Bethe Putney
text: First time trying this place. Ordered a gluten free pizza and a Chicago deep dish, and mozzarella sticks.  The pizza crusts were both good, we both enjoyed our respective pizzas. Pizza sauce is really good, cheese and pepperoni both good as …More

name: Nicole Lopez
text: Pizza is amazing. They even cut it in squares like in Chicago. I'm from Chicago but now reside in Winter Park & happy I finally found a pizza spot that tastes like home.

name: Journey
text: Great food and amazing front desk people. Stopped by and got a jumbo slice and it was amazing.

name: M Orr
text: The food was decent. Just disappointed in the portion size (when you spend $30 for food they should give you a decent sizes portion) also my pizza was a little hard

name: Girthwurm Jim
text: I live in Orlando for almost 7 years now and I've been looking for a good thin crust pizza aside from a fast food chain. …More

name: Linda bartholomae Linda
text:
Ordered  deep dish pizza with bacon,peporoni. Pizza was extremely salty
Couldnt taste bacon. Hardly any on pizza. Tomato sauce was extremely strong. We wont order again.

name: James Harper
text: Absolutely delicious and hands down one of the best pizzerias introduced to florida! Really reminds me of back home in Chicago

name: Gabriel Diaz
text: First time having deep dish pizza and my finance and I were pleasantly surprised. Ingredients tasted high quality and everything tasted great.

name: Allison Forgus
text: So I am very familiar with Rosati's when they had a few locations open in Colorado. It used to be my go-to on many Friday nights for years. After moving to Florida I was happy to see a location open up here. I ordered my standard thin crust …More

name: Alex
text: First time here. Pizza should not be overcooked. The cheese and the crust get hard and you can’t enjoy it. Both of my slices turned out this way. Bummer. #1 pizza rule, don’t burn the cheese. So far will not be returning.

name: Mr Wabbitt
text: Cheefs sub was pretty good. Filled with meat n cheese. Au jus was alittle spicy but ok. Cheesesticks were meh for the price. Mom enjoyed her quarantine spaghetti. Would have given 5 stars but disappointed they were out of the Dr Pepper I ordered.

name: Jay Piechocki
text: As a former Chicagoan this pizza is perfect from this home town store

name: Chelle C.P.
text: Food is just like home!  Staff is always friendly.

name: Addie Blomquist
text: We stopped here for lunch on the way back from our trip. We had a group of 10 (4 adults, 6 teenagers 13-16). We waited about 30 mins, which for a group that size is OK. The pizza was very good I thought and the teenagers loved it. The staff that we had was great and very friendly. Can definitely recommend this place.

name: Jose Venegas
text: Excellent pasta dish.  I had onions, fresh peppers, and garlic.  So good!

name: Jennifer Miller
text: Holy dough nuggets! This place is legit. We don’t get Chicago style often but when we do, it’s from Rosati’s.

name: Psy Tron
text: Think I bumped into the manager or owner not too sure but  they  whipped me  up a custom order since Stromboli's aren't  on the menu. It came out fantastic. The team there seemed eager to cook and serve. The crust on the Stromboli was …More

name: enid prather
text: I am in love with this place. The pizza is  made fresh, with fresh ingredients and nice thin crust.

name: Robert Bates
text: Amazing pizza, even better Italian Beef/Sausage combo! OMG, Chicago has made it's way to Orlando!

name: Harvet Jones
text: Great pizza they arent like the lame ny style pizza wit no sauce and hardly any cheese

name: Gary Lanman
text: I've been waiting for GREAT PIZZA since I moved to Florida and it's finally here! Every time I order pizza or sandwiches it's perfect. Just open one by Sanford so I don't have to drive so far.

name: Cici Lewis
text: I got Food  poisoning from eating here so I wouldn’t recommend it!

name: Jack
text: Pizza and "donut" bread was good.  The dine in area is very limited, two table's and some counter top seating.

name: Triforce Corgis
text:
Ordered for the first time a couple nights ago. Was dying to try these guys out.
Spent 30-something bucks on a deep dish to be delivered. …More

name: Robyn Nelson
text: Truly amazing Chicago style pizza, it's my favorite and I've tried many.  Never disappointed, from the dough nuggets to the zeppoli.  Thank you for making such a great product!

name: Amber Kanchwala
text: Amazing experience. The quality of this pizza is by far the best in the area!! Great customer service too, a true Chicago feel.

name: zahra huda
text: True Chicago style pizza. Very different form any other pizza we tried. It was our first time trying Rosatis 18 inch pizza thin crust loaded with toppings and cheesy in every bite. Mango Herbenaro wings were spicy with a sweet ting and kids also enjoyed boneless wings.

name: ARIANA MERCHANT
text: Wow! I am just amazed by this place. The pizza was not what I expected. In fact, it was 100 times better. I’m so glad I came here. It’s truly the best experience ever. So, if you want some pizza/pasta/wings/sandwiches, come here and trust me, you will not regret it! I love it!

name: Taz Tharoo
text: Our team loved the thin crust pizza and the Mango Habanero wings for our office luncheon.  Would definitely recommend it and come back!

name: Jose Lugo
text: The pizza was very good, plenty of cheese and sauce. Everyone was friendly. Would come back.

name: Robert Jacobs
text: We ordered online and had to do so 6 times on two different phones before our order was accepted. Their online ordering is terrible. …More

name: Kelley Wilson
text: It was overcooked and I had requested easy cook, when I complained the manager said all ovens are different. Rather then say he didn't know how to bake easy cook. There was no meat on the pizza just mushrooms, spinach, jalapeno and extra …More

name: Maria Cortes
text: We ordered a 14" thin crust with sausage and pepperoni and a 14" deep dish with sausage, green peppers and onions. The thin crust pizza had toppings from crust to crust and saucy. The deep dish had tons of cheese and a delicious chunky tomato sauce with a buttery crust. Just like in Chicago. We will be back!

name: Nick Massoni
text: I was excited to try this new addition to my neighborhood. I thought the price seemed a little high but I’ll always pay for quality. Very disappointed. I ordered the special that includes a 14” pizza with two toppings, a side and a two …More

name: Dale Segvich
text: Been to a lot of Rosati’s locations across the country, and Winter Park you are DA BEST!!! Let’s knock that wall down and quadruple the space and the business! Will definitely be back, as a matter of fact, I’ll be there 2-Night, and Jimmy, You are the best thank you for the great service and great pizza!

name: Paula Abraham
text: Excellent food and service. Owner goes above and beyond and I can’t recommend this place enough. Wings were amazing and pizza as well

name: Vera Lupolova
text: Family owned business. Friendly staff, Cozy and welcoming place, pizza was so great what we decided to try all the choices! would recommend this place to everyone and definitely coming back!

name: Un Known
text: Pizza is good either hot or cold

name: Sophia Wasu
text: True Chicago taste of pizza in Orlando. Better than the rest. @aquickspoonful on Instagram.

name: Eric Wampner
text: Chicago style! Stopped by for lunch and my friends and I split a roast beef sandwich and a 14" deep dish pie, way too much food for the three of us, but it was great. Finished off with zeppole, tasty! Note that there is extremely limited seating inside.

name: Jason Adorno
text: Should consider training the employees. And off bundle deals that are sitting right o the counter. Instead of charging across the board.

name: Amanda Schaefer
text: We ordered food for five online and all truly enjoyed their choices. My youngest is a connoisseur of spaghetti and meatballs and gave Rosati's an almost perfect rating. The calzone and Italian beef and chicken parmesan sadlndwiches were all …More

name: Sheila O'Ben
text: Chicago Style pizza in Central Florida! So yummy! Pizza always tastes better when cut into squares. LOL. So glad we found this place! …More

name: Irfan Sherali
text: Great food, great service. Highly recommend it.

name: Margaret Chalarca
text: Ordered the thin crust pizza with pepperoni, onions and green peppers. It was delicious!

name: Jennifer Milton
text: Ordered the windy city 16" pizza. The pizza was hot and fresh farcary from some of the other pizzas joints in the area. Will check them out again.

name: tamie mccay
text: Hands down the best pizza place in the area.

name: Catheryn Major
text: The spaghetti was pretty good, but the Zeppole WAS AMAZING!! Tasted just like beignets from Cafe Du Monde!! So fresh, so warm, so sweet! *sighs* I ate the whole order by myself😂. Reminded me of home! Totally worth the price, I'm shocked that they aren't more expensive!

name: Edwin Lopez
text: Excellent Chicago style Pizza. Best in the area. Love the deep dish. Phenominal pie. Management was exceptionally profesional. Fast delivery too. Highly recomend it. No more New York Style Pizza for me.

name: Steve Marshall
text: Excellent food and a good price. I will go back
